\begin_layout Standard
Ricordando che: 
\begin_inset Formula $R^{*}=\frac{R}{M}$
\end_inset

 e ponendo 
\begin_inset Formula $m=NM$
\end_inset

 costante apparente del gas, si ha:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\size large
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
M_{m}=\frac{m_{m}}{N_{m}}=\frac{m_{m}}{\sum_{i=1}^{k}\frac{m_{i}}{M_{i}}}=\frac{1}{\sum_{i=1}^{k}\frac{m_{i}}{m_{mM_{i}}}}=\frac{1}{\sum_{i=1}^{k}\frac{mf_{i}}{M_{i}}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Frazione in massa e frazione molare di una miscela sono in relazione fra
 loro:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\size large
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
